results.name: First differences of A280774.
comment: Let s(m) = A280864(m). The sequence gives the lengths of successive segments when A280864 is split after any term s(m) where every prime divisor of s(m) has already divided s(m-1). (Then s(m+1) is the smallest number not yet in A280864 which is relatively prime to s(m).)
See the link "Properties of A280864" in A280864 for more information.
link: N. J. A. Sloane, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..25317
